overview: The user tasked the assistant with adding database capabilities and an
  admin dashboard to a sleep questionnaire application. The assistant began by
  evaluating the existing codebase against the SOW, identifying the need for a
  response database, CSV export, and an admin interface with authentication.
  After clarifying user preferences for simple password authentication and
  specific demographic fields, a comprehensive plan was developed. The
  implementation involved updating data models, creating API routes for
  questionnaire submission and data retrieval, and building a basic admin
  dashboard. A significant pivot occurred when the authentication system was
  refactored to leverage Next.js middleware for a cleaner and simpler approach
  to route protection. The database was successfully set up using NeonDB, and
  initial browser tests confirmed the admin login and API endpoints were
  functional, though a complete end-to-end test of form submission to the
  database was still in progress.
